.TH HELLO_GFORTRAN_O2 1 "" "" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hello_gfortran_O2 \- recovered Fortran program built with gfortran -O2
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hello_gfortran_O2
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hello_gfortran_O2
is a program recovered from a binary originally written in Fortran and
compiled with
.BR gfortran (1)
at optimization level
.BR -O2 .
The recovered source tree is C and consists of a small entry-point shim that
bootstraps the GNU Fortran runtime and dispatches to the Fortran main program.
.PP
The executable is intended to be invoked directly. It does not define any
application-specific command-line interface; any option handling present is
that provided by the Fortran runtime itself.
.SH OPTIONS
.B hello_gfortran_O2
does not define program-specific options. Arguments are passed through to
the Fortran runtime as supplied by the operating system.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gfortran (1),
.BR cmake (1)
